            Will the hon. Gentleman admit that, under the Conservative Administration, the health service was also regularly in crisis&#x2014;to use his description? If he read the same reports on delayed discharges in hospitals
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_76wh' title='Col. 76WH &mdash; HC Deb 31 January 2001 vol 362 c76WH' name='column_76wh' href='#column_76wh' rel='bookmark'>76WH</a>
            under the previous Administration, he would find exactly the same problem. Statistics on the number of people who waited on trolleys under that Administration show that the problem was the same. I should be interested to know how many times, between 1994 and 1997, he wrote to his local Member of Parliament about those issues. The problems have existed for a long time.
