          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0362P0_20010131_WH_64' title='Link to this speech by Ms Gisela Stuart' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-gisela-stuart" title="Ms Gisela Stuart">Ms Stuart</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I shall give way to the right hon. Gentleman.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0362P0_20010131_WH_65'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/earl-of-ancram' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0362P0_20010131_WH_65' title='Link to this speech by Earl of Ancram' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/earl-of-ancram" title="Earl of Ancram">Mr. Ancram</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I put four sensible and moderate suggestions to the Minister. I am looking forward to hearing her response to them.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0362P0_20010131_WH_66'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-gisela-stuart' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0362P0_20010131_WH_66' title='Link to this speech by Ms Gisela Stuart' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-gisela-stuart" title="Ms Gisela Stuart">Ms Stuart</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I was outlining the whole package, and I was also making the point that the standard spending assessment review is on-going. There is a debate about that this afternoon. However, this debate is about bed blocking, and I am talking about how the NHS and social services work together. The extra packages that have been put in place in Wiltshire have led to the Princess Margaret hospital receiving an additional &#x00A3;408,000 for its modernisation fund. Wiltshire and Swindon are increasing spending on personal social services.</p><p>
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_89wh' title='Col. 89WH &mdash; HC Deb 31 January 2001 vol 362 c89WH' name='column_89wh' href='#column_89wh' rel='bookmark'>89WH</a>
            Hon. Members have singularly failed to recognise the progress that has been made. I am not saying that the system is perfect. However, the solutions we propose are extra funding in the short term and a restructuring of services in the long term, which, as the right hon. Gentleman said, is not a matter of shifting hardship, but of solving the underlying problems. It is a 10-year plan, and we are well on the way. Conservative Members have no solutions other than arguing over figures that simply do not add up.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
